Dr Zoe Waller suffers from the skin condition dermatographia . 
  This is a type of urticaria - where a raised, itchy rash appears on the skin . 
  She teaches pharmacy at the University of East Anglia . 
  She uses her skin to teach her students about new drugs and molecules . 
  Whenever she draws on her skin, raised red weals appear . 
  She was diagnosed with the condition two years ago and uses it as a teaching aid . 
 